entries.title: U.S. to Require Travelers From China to Test Negative for Covid-19
entries.description: Federal health officials said the move reflects the coronavirus’s rapid spread in China.

entries.title: Turkey, Syria Defense Ministers Meet in Moscow
entries.description: The gathering was the first formal, high-level meeting between the two Middle East governments since the eruption of a civil war in Syria in 2011.

entries.title: With Title 42 Still in Place, Migrants Wait in Mexican Border Cities and Weigh Options
entries.description: Thousands of migrants amassed at the U.S.-Mexico border were expecting pandemic-era controls to end and planning to request asylum

entries.title: Benjamin Netanyahu Signs Coalition Deals Ahead of Expected Return to Power
entries.description: Israel’s incoming prime minister finalized coalition deals on Wednesday, a day before he is set to return to power as leader of the most right-wing and religious government in the country’s history.

entries.title: Ukraine Sets Sights on Retaking Key Eastern City
entries.description: Taking Kreminna could mark a breakthrough for Ukraine’s efforts to dislodge the Russian occupation of its east.

entries.title: EU Foreign-Subsidy Limits Target China, but Also Hit U.S.
entries.description: Under rules taking effect next year, the Inflation Reduction Act and other aid could trigger hefty reporting requirements, competition lawyers say.

entries.title: China Increases Trade in Asia as U.S. Pushes Toward Decoupling
entries.description: The deepening ties are a result of China’s regional heft but also Washington’s spat with Beijing.

entries.title: Russia's War Has United Europe, but Highlights Bloc's Dependence on U.S.
entries.description: Russian President Vladimir Putin’s energy war has failed to deter European Union countries from backing Ukraine, but many fear an endless conflict.

entries.title: Pope Francis Says Retired Pope Benedict XVI Is 'Very Sick'
entries.description: Pope Francis said his 95-year-old predecessor, retired Pope Benedict XVI, was very ill and asked the faithful to pray for him.

entries.title: China's Censors End Crackdown on Covid-Policy Criticism---of a Certain Kind
entries.description: Protesters and public-health experts have been targeted for blame for the country’s sudden about-face as infections explode, but leader Xi Jinping remains unscathed.
